dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Turnu-Severin, sheet R-23/24. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4375)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4375. Alternate title: Turnu-Severin, Romania. Transverse Mercator projection. Universal transverse Mercator and Danube zone grids. UTM grid added, gradient tints and isogonic data deleted by AMS, 1948. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With Romanian, Serb and Croat, and Bulgarian glossaries. Corrected from Intellgence Reports up to Jan. 1944. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete. Geographic designation is given as Yugoslavia its is Serbia and Montenegro.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1948.
